 by the ratio 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{\zeta}_{f,j}/\bar{\zeta}_{f}$
\end_inset

 (see Proposition X).
 To put some more intuition behind this result, note that with many buyers
 a supplier allocates a smaller share of its R&D expenditure to each of
 those buyers.
