noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 also clarifies why selection into R&D locations is a first-order concern.
 Firms choose their R&D and production locations in the entry, anticipating
 the payoffs characterized here.
 A firm that anticipates concentrated sales has strong incentive to locate
 near that buyer's manufacturing - hence high 
\begin_inset Formula $\zeta_{f,j,c}$
\end_inset

 for some 
\begin_inset Formula $c$
\end_inset

 and high 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{\zeta}_{f,j}/\bar{\zeta}_{f}$
\end_inset

.
 Conversely, a supplier that anticipate servings many buyers has stronger
