 motivate a reduced-form specification that allows the effects of proximity
 and scale to vary systematically with buyer concentration:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\begin{alignedat}{1}\log\text{Patents}_{i,p,c,t} & \sim\log\text{Quantity}_{i,p,t}+\text{BCI}_{i,p,t}\times\log\text{Quantity}_{i,p,t}+\text{BCI}_{i,p,t}+\\
 & +\log\text{Upstream Proximity}_{i,p,t,c}+\text{BCI}_{i,p,t}\times\log\text{Upstream Proximity}_{i,p,t,c}\\
 & +\log\text{Downstream Proximity}_{i,p,t,c}+\text{BCI}_{i,p,t}\times\log\text{Downstream Proximity}_{i,p,t,c}\\
 & +\delta_{i,t,c}+\delta_{p,t,c}+\omega_{i,p,t,c}
\end{alignedat}
\label{eq:Main-Specification}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where we unpack the index 
\begin_inset Formula $f\equiv\left(i,p,t\right)$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(\text{supplier},\text{part},\text{year}\right)$
\end_inset

, to be explicit about the units of observation and dimensions of variables.
 This specification implements the model's two central reduced-form implications.
