\begin_layout Standard
The choice of fixed effects serves two roles.
 The part-country-year effect 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta_{p,t,c}$
\end_inset

 absorbs country-year variation in R&D costs 
\begin_inset Formula $r_{c}$
\end_inset

 and local characteristics such as knowledge stocks 
\begin_inset Formula $K_{p,c}$
\end_inset

 and part-country-specific differences in patenting intensity.
 The firm-country-year effect 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta_{i,t,c}$
\end_inset

 absorbs firm-location shocks that jointly affect manufacturing proximity
 and innovation.
 This includes persistent firm-location preferences, local subsidies, and
 time-varying firm activity in a country.
 
\end_layout

