\begin_layout Standard
To address this concern, we examine two robustness checks.
 First, I estimate alternate zero-stage specifications that omit firm controls,
 ensuring that variation comes only from tariffs rather than differences
 in the estimated firm fixed effects.
 This, however, does require different assumptions on properties of the
 IV.
 Namely, that variation in tariffs rates across firms and countries is valid
 for identification.
 Second, I implement the recentering correction from 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "Borusyak.Hull2021"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 One can think of the fixed effects, which capture baseline production/sales
 probabilities, as inducing non-random exposure to the shocks through the
 construction of the instrument.
