\begin_layout Subsection
Structural Estimation for Upstream Firms
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The reduced-firm estimates provide evidence for the model's mechanisms,
 but outside of the very special cases like those in Proposition 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "prop: Reduced Form Log Patents"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

, the estimates are not generally identifying structural parameters.
 Therefore, I estimate the model using Generalized Method of Moments (GMM).
 The estimation is centered on moment conditions using two residuals: an
 R&D productivity residuals 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon_{f,c}$
\end_inset

 that rationalizes patent outcomes and a demand residuals 
\begin_inset Formula $\xi_{f,m}$
\end_inset

 that fits observed sourcing shares.
 To characterize the estimation strategy I first impose additional measurement
 assumptions that map observables to model objects, and second invert the
 model can be inverted for the unique set of residuals conditional on parameters.
 Finally, I specify the identification assumptions that utilize the instruments
 introduced in Table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab: Reduced Form Estimation"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

.
