n 
\begin_inset Formula $c_{f,m}$
\end_inset

 and innovation 
\begin_inset Formula $r_{c}$
\end_inset

 costs, and then show how 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon_{f,c}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\xi_{f,m}$
\end_inset

 can be uniquely recovered under the assumptions of this section.
 Afterwards, we turn to the identification assumptions and incorporate the
 instruments introduced in Table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab: Reduced Form Estimation"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\end_inset


