 residuals, and not those that contain the demand residual.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
We view Row 4 as making the weakest set of assumptions.
 Namely, we do not require the model to also explain demand shares - we
 simply take the level of demand as given and try to predict aspects of
 patenting - allowing us to make direct comparisons to the reduced-form
 results.
 By contrast in Row 1, we require that the model predict true productivity
 differences such that demand shares are best rationalized by the model.
 Row 1 we take to the data in quantitative exercises to come, but Row 4
 allows us to make direct comparisons to the reduced-firm results thus far.
 
\end_layout

\end_inset

