\begin_layout Subsubsection
Characterizing the R&D Allocation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Here we characterize how OEMs allocate innovation across assembly and parts
 as well as across R&D facilities.
 The key difference, relative to the supplier's allocation, is that OEMs
 part-level innovations enter a CES production function, and thus can not
 be treated as separable decisions within the firm.
 Depending on the degree of substitutability between inputs, R&D expenditures
 across parts will either be complements or substitutes.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To characterize the R&D allocations for OEMs, just as with suppliers, it
 will be useful to define both R&D productivity indices and cost aggregates
 over the sales locations of OEMs.
 For 
\begin_inset Formula $x\in\left\{ A,\mathcal{P}\right\} $
\end_inset

 (assembly and the set of parts), the following index summarizes the effective
 cost of raising innovation:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\bar{\zeta}_{j,x}=\left(\sum_{c}\left[\zeta_{j,x}r_{c}^{-\zeta}\right]^{\frac{\varsigma}{1-\varsigma}}\right)^{\frac{1-\varsigma}{\varsigma}}.\label{eq: R&D Productivity Shifters - OEM}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

This index incorporate both productivity advantages and R&D costs, and accounts
 for the optimal allocation of R&D across countries implied by the CES structure.
 Next, I define OEM-level aggregates over markets: 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\bar{q}_{j}=\sum_{k}q_{j,k}\text{ and }\bar{p}_{j,p}=\sum_{k}\frac{q_{j,k}}{\bar{q}_{j}}p_{j,p,k},\bar{c}_{j,A}=\sum_{k}\frac{q_{j,k}}{\bar{q}_{j}}c_{j,A,k}.
\]

\end_inset

The term 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{q}_{j}$
\end_inset

 denotes total sales from OEM 
\begin_inset Formula $j$
\end_inset

 cross all markets, while 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{c}_{j,A}$
\end_inset

 (
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{p}_{j,p}$
\end_inset

) is the corresponding quantity-weighted average assembly cost (input price).
 These aggregates summarize the scale and cost conditions relevant for character
izing R&D allocation across inputs.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Proposition
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "prop: OEMs R&D Allocation"

\end_inset

Downstream OEMs allocate their R&D as follows:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\shape italic
a relative allocation across parts and assembly that for any 
\begin_inset Formula $x\in\left\{ A,\mathcal{P}\right\} $
\end_inset

 satisfies
\shape default

\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{I_{j,x}}{\sum_{p}I_{j,p}+I_{j,A}}=\frac{\left(\left(\chi_{j,x}\bar{c}_{j,x}\right)^{1-\nu}\bar{\zeta}_{j,x}\right)^{\frac{1}{1+\rho\left(1-\nu\right)}}}{\sum_{p}\left(\left(\chi_{j,p}\bar{c}_{j,p}\right)^{1-\nu}\bar{\zeta}_{j,p}\right)^{\frac{1}{1+\rho\left(1-\nu\right)}}+\left(\left(\chi_{j,A}\bar{c}_{j,A}\right)^{1-\nu}\bar{\zeta}_{j,A}\right)^{\frac{1}{1+\rho\left(1-\nu\right)}}},
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

