\begin_layout Assumption
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "assu: Observability of Innovation - OEM"

\end_inset

Observability of Innovation.
 Patents measure model innovations:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\text{Patents}_{f,x,c}=\left(I_{f,x}^{\eta}\right)^{\gamma}\times\frac{I_{f,x,c}\zeta_{f,x,c}}{\sum I_{f,x,c}\zeta_{f,x,c}}\implies\text{Patents}_{f,x}=\left(I_{f,x}^{\eta}\right)^{\gamma}\label{eq: Patent Equation - OEM}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Because two sets of residuals shape the distribution of patents across-countries
 ( 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon_{j,x,c}$
\end_inset

) and across parts ( 
\begin_inset Formula $\chi_{j,x}$
\end_inset

), I require a normalization for unique inversion of the model.
 Hence, I additionally assume that 
\begin_inset Formula $\sum_{c}\varepsilon_{f,x,c}=1$
\end_inset

.
 
