 reports GMM estimates for the OEM model.
 I begin with quantifying the return to OEM innovation.
 In the model, R&D lowers marginal costs with elasticity 
\begin_inset Formula $\eta$
\end_inset

, and demand responds to costs with elasticity 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma$
\end_inset

.
 This implied elasticity of output with respect to R&D is therefore
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{d\log\text{Output}_{j}}{d\log\text{R\&D}_{j}}=\frac{d\log\text{Output}_{j}}{d\log\text{Cost}_{j}}\times\frac{d\log\text{Cost}_{j}}{d\log\text{R\&D}_{j}}=\sigma\times\eta=0.136.
\]

\end_inset

For comparison, the corresponding elasticity for suppliers is 
